Five herdsmen have been sentenced to life imprisonment by the Kwara State High Court for offences of kidnapping and illegal possession of firearms. In the judgement which was handed down by Justice Hannah Ajayi, the convicted herdsmen; Tambaya Abubakar, Babuga Umaru, Shehu Umaru, Mojumba Bello, Abubakar Juli and Mamma Lawali were found guilty as charged. According to the charge before the court, the convicts conspired and kidnapped one Usman Mohammed while armed with two single barrel guns at Osi, Ekiti local government area of the state. The charge further revealed that the convicts took Mohammed into the bush where they demanded ransom and N400,000 was paid by the victim’s family. The Director of Public Prosecution, Barrister Abdulmumini Adebimpe Jimoh (SAN), who prosecuted the matter, expressed satisfaction over the judge’s verdict saying it will serve as a deterrent to others who may want to indulge in such act. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Five herdsmen sentenced  Five herdsmen sentenced Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Five herdsmen sentenced  Five herdsmen sentenced How Adetunji Made over N20million in 2021 from Football Trading. Click Here to Join his team